cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with using neural networks to generate images of faces from low-dimensional embeddings. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves training a separate neural network to solve the minimization problem, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that the paper could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves optimizing the loss function, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
